  "prompt": "How should I prepare for Phd at IIT or IISc in computer science?",
  "response": "To prepare for a PhD in Computer Science at IIT or IISc, consider the following steps:\n\n1. Academic Preparation\n- Maintain a high CGPA (preferably 8.5+)\n- Focus on strong fundamentals in Computer Science\n- Take advanced courses in your area of interest\n- Publish research papers in reputable conferences/journals\n- Develop strong programming and research skills\n\n2. Research Experience\n- Participate in research projects during UG/PG\n- Work with professors on research publications\n- Attend workshops and seminars\n- Gain research internship experience\n- Develop expertise in a specific research area\n\n3. Entrance Exam Preparation\n- Prepare for GATE/NET\n- Study advanced CS subjects thoroughly\n- Practice previous years' question papers\n- Take mock tests\n- Focus on algorithms, data structures, operating systems\n\n4. Skill Development\n- Strong mathematical foundations\n- Programming skills (Python, C++, Java)\n- Machine learning and AI knowledge\n- Research methodology\n- Technical writing skills\n\n5. Application Strategy\n- Research faculty profiles and research areas\n- Contact potential supervisors\n- Prepare a strong statement of purpose\n- Obtain solid recommendation letters\n- Highlight research achievements\n\n6. Additional Recommendations\n- Learn research tools and frameworks\n- Improve communication skills\n- Build a strong online research profile\n- Participate in coding competitions",
